A spatial analysis of Italian cafes names

Stefano De Sabbata

2022-04-08 08:43:12

Aims

Work in progress! :sweat_smile:

The aim is to replicate the work presented by Chris Brunsdon, Paul Harris and Lex Comber at GIRSRUK 2022, in the paper “A Spatial Analysis of British Public House Names”.

Preparation

Libraris

library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
library(knitr)
library(sf)
library(tmap)
#library(ggmap)
library(leaflet)
library(tidytext)

Data

This analysis uses OpenStreetMap open data, licensed under the Open Data Commons Open Database License (ODbL) by the OpenStreetMap Foundation (OSMF) © OpenStreetMap contributors.

cafes_Italy <- read_sf("../data/cafes-Italy-2022-04-07-16-17-16.geojson")

Overview map

tm_shape(cafes_Italy) + 
  tm_dots(col = "red") +
  tm_credits("© OpenStreetMap contributors")

Text content overview

cafes_Italy %>% 
  st_drop_geometry() %>% 
  filter(!is.na(name)) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, name) %>% 
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>% 
  slice_max(order_by = n, n = 100) %>% 
  kable()

Term-specific maps

“centrale”

leaflet(
    cafes_Italy %>% 
    filter(
      name %>% 
        str_to_lower() %>% 
        str_detect("centrale")
    )
  ) %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addProviderTiles(providers$Stamen.Toner) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(
    radius = 5,
    color = "red",
    popup = ~as.character(name), 
    label = ~as.character(name)
  )

“osteria”

leaflet(
    cafes_Italy %>% 
    filter(
      name %>% 
        str_to_lower() %>% 
        str_detect("osteria")
    )
  ) %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addProviderTiles(providers$Stamen.Toner) %>% 
  addCircleMarkers(
    radius = 5,
    color = "red",
    popup = ~as.character(name), 
    label = ~as.character(name)
  )

References
